description: It almost seemed unreal, how beautiful the mountains looked during sunset. Almost like a painting. The entire time the sun was setting, we all just were silent and in awe of how beautiful our earth is.

After the Snowstorm in Sumida, Tokyo: The rooftops, now blanketed in snow, catch the gentle glow of the setting sun, turning a soft orange. To the left flows the Sumida River, and further back, the Arakawa River stretches out. A faint rainbow arches across the sky, adding a touch of magic to the serene winter landscape.

I was freezing cold staying in the tent cabins in Half Dome (formerly Curry) Village in Yosemite Valley with my dad who was there for work, so I got up and drove around the valley at 6 am. There’s been lots of fires in the area and the valley was filled with this thick smoke. Stopped at a turnout near Tunnel View and shot this photo - I really love the symmetry of it and the smooth gradients the smoke produces.

Pink toned thoughts on a hike —
Everything comes in waves,
even mountains.

I had been travelling around Central America, living in a van and sharing experiences with other travelers.  Having just dropped my last travel buddy off I headed back to Lake Atitlan and found an incredible spot to camp right next to the lake.  There was this jetty sticking out into the lake where I sat watching the sunset, once again living the dream on my own. I knew something special was happening there, and now it has become BitcoinLake!

I think the best time to visit Yosemite is February. There is still some snow around the valley. The trees and the snow shine mystically because of the sun rays through the patchy clouds. Certainly a sight to behold.

Possibly the most peaceful and beautiful 2 hour hike you’ll ever do. Massive old growth trees, ancient temples, calming rivers, and a lush forest follows you along the entire route. When we reached the temple at the top, nobody was up there but an older Japanese woman reciting chants, while a monk slowly beat on a large drum.
